problem:
Let \[f(n) = \left\{
\begin{array}{cl}
n^2-2 & \text{ if }n<0, \\
2n-20 & \text{ if }n \geq 0.
\end{array}
\right.\]What is the positive difference between the two values of $a$ that satisfy the equation $f(-3)+f(3)+f(a)=0$?

The rules for a race require that all runners start at $A$, touch any part of the 1000-meter wall, then immediately run towards $B$ and finish at $B$. What is the number of meters in the minimum distance a participant must run? Express your answer to the nearest meter. [asy]
import olympiad; import geometry; size(250);
defaultpen(linewidth(0.8));
draw((0,3)--origin--(10,0)--(10,5));
label("300 m",(0,3)--origin,W); label("1000 m",(0,0)--(10,0),S); label("500 m",(10,0)--(10,5),E);
draw((0,3)--(6,0)--(10,5),linetype("3 3")+linewidth(0.7));
label("$A$",(0,3),N); label("$B$",(10,5),N);
[/asy]

